WEBVTT

1
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:01.940
We've gone as far as we can go by road.

2
00:01:02.650 --> 00:01:04.150
We need a boat.

3
00:01:04.990 --> 00:01:07.700
Should only take a few days.

4
00:01:07.700 --> 00:01:10.120
No. no. no. We shouldn't be here.

5
00:01:10.490 --> 00:01:12.370
The jungle doesn't want us here.

6
00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:14.450
There is...

7
00:01:45.990 --> 00:01:47.990
We have to do this.

8
00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:51.030
What's waiting for us
will change our lives.

9
00:01:52.580 --> 00:01:53.660
Eh?

10
00:01:53.660 --> 00:01:54.750
Fine.

11
00:01:55.620 --> 00:01:56.500
I'll go alone.

12
00:01:56.500 --> 00:01:57.500
Ana.

13
00:01:58.080 --> 00:01:59.040
Ana!

14
00:01:59.880 --> 00:02:01.130
Don't do this!

15
00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:19.350
It's her.

16
00:02:30.410 --> 00:02:31.820
Get to the boat!

17
00:02:40.330 --> 00:02:41.920
Come on! Let's go!

18
00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:44.840
- Hey!
- Stop!

19
00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:46.510
Take my hand!

20
00:03:04.230 --> 00:03:05.980
<i>We start tight on a full moon.</i>

21
00:03:07.110 --> 00:03:09.450
<i>Milky. Almost yellow.</i>

22
00:03:10.700 --> 00:03:12.070
<i>And we crane down</i>

23
00:03:12.950 --> 00:03:17.160
<i>to reveal an idyllic. suburban street.</i>

24
00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:21.540
<i>We float past a series
of white picket fences.</i>

25
00:03:21.540 --> 00:03:23.420
<i>until we settle on a sewer grate.</i>

26
00:03:24.590 --> 00:03:26.000
Pow! Flies open!

27
00:03:26.670 --> 00:03:29.420
Something big and scaly slithers out.

28
00:03:29.420 --> 00:03:32.720
fast. hungry. definitely not human.

29
00:03:32.720 --> 00:03:35.050
as a pulsating score kicks in.

30
00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:46.060
We're on the back of the beast

31
00:03:46.070 --> 00:03:49.320
as it slithers menacingly
towards a little blue house.

32
00:04:02.710 --> 00:04:04.370
Wait. I'm sorry.

33
00:04:04.380 --> 00:04:07.420
This is our wedding video
you're talking about?

34
00:04:07.420 --> 00:04:11.380
Yes. though I actually don't think of them
as videos. They're more like short films.

35
00:04:11.380 --> 00:04:15.720
Yeah. because I'm not sure
this is quite what we had in mind.

36
00:04:15.720 --> 00:04:17.970
Okay. I know.
It's a little different than normal but--

37
00:04:17.970 --> 00:04:20.970
We really liked the one you did
for Karen and Bart.

38
00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:22.430
When they walk by the river

39
00:04:22.430 --> 00:04:24.770
- and jump up and high-five.
- That jump was dope.

40
00:04:24.770 --> 00:04:26.230
And I loved that song they used.

41
00:04:26.230 --> 00:04:30.280
<i>♪ I don't want to wait
For our lives to be over ♪</i>

42
00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:34.240
<i>♪ I want to know right now
How does it feel ♪</i>

43
00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:37.120
- You know it. Yeah.
- Um. guys. Uh. here's the thing.

44
00:04:37.120 --> 00:04:40.200
I really like you guys.
And you said you're horror fans.

45
00:04:40.200 --> 00:04:42.330
and I'm like. "I love horror so much."

46
00:04:42.330 --> 00:04:45.160
And I thought this could be special.
You know what I mean?

47
00:04:45.170 --> 00:04:47.790
This is a film you're gonna watch
for the rest of your lives.

48
00:04:47.790 --> 00:04:49.920
But this isn't a film. Doug.

49
00:04:49.920 --> 00:04:53.760
This is a wedding video. and we want one
where they do a little jump.

50
00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:55.880
- Yeah.
- Now. can you do that for us or not?

51
00:05:03.100 --> 00:05:04.430
Okay.

52
00:05:04.440 --> 00:05:07.560
And do you mind if I'm doing warm-ups?
Is it okay?

53
00:05:07.560 --> 00:05:09.560
Oh. yeah. I've seen much crazier.

54
00:05:09.570 --> 00:05:10.650
Okay. good.

55
00:05:10.650 --> 00:05:13.190
Does it sound better to say my line.

56
00:05:13.190 --> 00:05:16.320
"His vision is blurry.
which <i>could</i> suggest..."

57
00:05:16.320 --> 00:05:19.530
or. "His vision is blurry.
which could <i>suggest</i>..."

58
00:05:19.530 --> 00:05:22.370
Or I could-- You know what? I could even
do. like. an accent. I could do just...

59
00:05:22.370 --> 00:05:25.000
I think you just should do it
the way you auditioned it. honey.

60
00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:26.080
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

61
00:05:26.080 --> 00:05:29.920
It's been a while since I booked anything.
and I just want it to go well.

62
00:05:29.920 --> 00:05:31.340
- Yeah.
- I just...

63
00:05:31.340 --> 00:05:32.880
It's hard out there.

64
00:05:33.460 --> 00:05:35.130
Sorry.

65
00:05:35.130 --> 00:05:37.010
Doctor number 3. we're ready for you.

66
00:05:37.010 --> 00:05:38.220
Okay. knock 'em dead.

67
00:05:38.220 --> 00:05:39.930
Okay. thanks. Thank you. Donna.

68
00:05:39.930 --> 00:05:42.560
Hey. by the way. if you ever
need anything from Lowe's.

69
00:05:42.560 --> 00:05:44.520
I will hook you up
with my employee discount.

70
00:05:44.520 --> 00:05:45.810
no questions asked.

71
00:05:46.310 --> 00:05:47.650
- Okay?
- Okay.

72
00:05:52.400 --> 00:05:55.030
Thanks. Ten more ccs of tramadol.

73
00:05:55.030 --> 00:05:56.780
Any idea what I'm looking at here?

74
00:05:56.780 --> 00:05:58.490
He said his vision was blurry.

75
00:05:58.490 --> 00:06:01.780
- so. you know. that could suggest--
- Optic neuritis.

76
00:06:02.580 --> 00:06:03.870
Already ruled that out.

77
00:06:03.870 --> 00:06:05.450
- Cut.
- That's a cut!

78
00:06:05.450 --> 00:06:07.750
Hey. buddy. not sure what that accent is.

79
00:06:07.750 --> 00:06:10.000
Just do it normally. okay?

80
00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:11.290
We're gonna go again right away.

81
00:06:11.290 --> 00:06:12.210
Set.

82
00:06:12.210 --> 00:06:17.010
He said his vision
was blurry. which could suggest--

83
00:06:17.010 --> 00:06:20.050
Cut! Say the line faster. Okay?
Faster this time.

84
00:06:20.050 --> 00:06:22.350
He said his vision was blurry.
which could suggest--

85
00:06:22.350 --> 00:06:24.850
Cut! Jesus.
I think we gotta fire this guy.

86
00:06:24.850 --> 00:06:26.560
Can we get somebody else in here?

87
00:06:40.320 --> 00:06:43.370
<i>♪ When it's over. so they say ♪</i>

88
00:06:44.120 --> 00:06:46.990
<i>♪ It'll rain a sunny day ♪</i>

89
00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:52.840
<i>♪ I know. shining down like water ♪</i>

90
00:06:57.090 --> 00:07:03.350
<i>♪ I wanna know
Have you ever seen the rain? ♪</i>

91
00:07:05.140 --> 00:07:06.350
<i>♪ I wanna know ♪</i>

92
00:07:07.390 --> 00:07:11.310
<i>♪ Have you ever seen the rain? ♪</i>

93
00:07:11.310 --> 00:07:15.270
<i>Griff. it's Doug. I just ran into
your mom at the supermarket.</i>

94
00:07:15.270 --> 00:07:17.230
<i>She said you booked a big gig today.</i>

95
00:07:17.940 --> 00:07:18.820
<i>I'm proud of you. bud.</i>

96
00:07:18.820 --> 00:07:21.150
<i>Everyone in Buffalo misses you.</i>

97
00:07:21.160 --> 00:07:23.740
<i>I love you. Come visit. man!</i>

98
00:07:25.660 --> 00:07:26.990
Jesus. Jerry.

99
00:07:26.990 --> 00:07:30.660
Doug. what is this thing about--
there's some kind of sewer monster?

100
00:07:31.460 --> 00:07:32.540
Oh. boy.

101
00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:35.540
Doug.

102
00:07:36.670 --> 00:07:40.670
Look. I get that this is not what
you dreamed about when you were a kid.

103
00:07:41.220 --> 00:07:43.340
But dreams. they go. Huh?

104
00:07:43.340 --> 00:07:45.340
Now. I'll be retiring soon.

105
00:07:45.350 --> 00:07:49.430
And. Doug. it is only a matter of time
before all this is yours.

106
00:07:49.430 --> 00:07:50.520
- Really?
- Yeah.

107
00:07:50.520 --> 00:07:52.900
Look around. Take it all in.

108
00:07:53.980 --> 00:07:55.270
And imagine.

109
00:07:57.020 --> 00:08:00.030
If you do it right.
it's a pretty sweet setup we got here.

110
00:08:00.030 --> 00:08:03.740
This is a B. and maybe even
a B+ life we're talking about.

111
00:08:05.950 --> 00:08:06.780
Hmm.

112
00:08:06.780 --> 00:08:10.040
Are you sure you don't wanna
do anything for your birthday?

113
00:08:10.540 --> 00:08:12.830
You used to make me
celebrate your half-birthdays.

114
00:08:14.170 --> 00:08:15.830
Let's go get a beer.

115
00:08:16.460 --> 00:08:17.750
Or something.

116
00:08:19.050 --> 00:08:21.510
Maybe we just watch that new
mountain climbing doc.

117
00:08:21.510 --> 00:08:24.550
About the lady that
falls to her own death?

118
00:08:25.050 --> 00:08:26.180
Yeah.

119
00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:30.850
Fine. we can do the one about
the free diver in the Maldives.

120
00:08:30.850 --> 00:08:33.520
Who drowns? Jesus Christ. Doug.

121
00:08:33.520 --> 00:08:35.810
I don't know. Let's just take a gummy
and go to bed early.

122
00:08:35.810 --> 00:08:37.610
Surprise!

123
00:08:39.230 --> 00:08:41.230
Oh. my God. Malie. No!

124
00:08:41.240 --> 00:08:44.070
Oh. yes. Yes. you love
a good. big birthday party.

125
00:08:44.070 --> 00:08:45.740
Dad. should've seen your face.

126
00:08:45.740 --> 00:08:47.660
- You knew about this?
- It was my idea.

127
00:08:47.660 --> 00:08:49.660
- Buddy. take my coat. please. Thank you.
- Okay.

128
00:08:49.660 --> 00:08:51.040
Hey! How are you?

129
00:08:51.040 --> 00:08:54.040
- Yeah. Happy birthday!
- Jesus. Kenny. My back!

130
00:08:54.040 --> 00:08:56.460
- I'm sorry.
- No! That's not...

131
00:08:56.460 --> 00:08:58.920
The actual lotion. The actual basket.

132
00:08:58.920 --> 00:09:00.710
"It puts the lotion in the basket"?

133
00:09:00.710 --> 00:09:02.670
- eBay. buddy.
- Dude. that is sick.

134
00:09:02.670 --> 00:09:04.720
Yeah. no. that is actually sick.

135
00:09:04.720 --> 00:09:05.930
Oh!

136
00:09:05.930 --> 00:09:09.430
- Happy birthday. Dougie.
- Thanks for making the trek. Claire.

137
00:09:09.430 --> 00:09:14.600
You know I love Buffalo this time of year.
The slush. the hypothermia.

138
00:09:14.600 --> 00:09:15.890
What's up? No Trent?

139
00:09:15.890 --> 00:09:17.230
No Trent.

140
00:09:17.230 --> 00:09:18.900
Ever again. in fact.

141
00:09:18.900 --> 00:09:21.150
- He started banging his dental hygienist.
- Ugh.

142
00:09:21.150 --> 00:09:24.070
Anyway. tonight is all about you. baby.

143
00:09:24.070 --> 00:09:25.780
- It's about me.
- It's about you.

144
00:09:28.990 --> 00:09:31.490
You came! Here you are. Oh. my God.

145
00:09:31.490 --> 00:09:32.580
It's been too long. pal.

146
00:09:32.580 --> 00:09:35.040
It's so good to see you.
It has been way too long.

147
00:09:35.040 --> 00:09:36.120
Happy birthday.

148
00:09:36.120 --> 00:09:37.830
Thank you for coming out here.

149
00:09:37.830 --> 00:09:39.330
- Think I'm gonna miss this? Never.
- Oh.

150
00:09:39.330 --> 00:09:41.040
We got a lot of catching up to do.

151
00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:46.840
Many years ago. a group of young.
passionate artists had a vision.

152
00:09:46.840 --> 00:09:52.560
It was a vision that's not
particularly original or even. uh. good...

153
00:09:52.560 --> 00:09:54.600
...but it was theirs.

154
00:09:54.600 --> 00:09:58.020
And so they made that vision a reality.

155
00:09:58.020 --> 00:10:00.650
And. without further ado.

156
00:10:00.650 --> 00:10:05.780
I present to you
a completely unrestored print

157
00:10:05.780 --> 00:10:10.910
of 13-year-old Doug McCallister's
masterpiece. <i>The Quatch</i>.

158
00:10:11.830 --> 00:10:13.950
What? I thought we lost
all the copies of that!

159
00:10:13.950 --> 00:10:15.040
- No way.
- Nope.

160
00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:17.910
I found it in my mom's garage.
It was stuck in the player.

161
00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:20.330
Are we sure this is okay
for the kids to watch?

162
00:10:20.330 --> 00:10:21.630
Who gives a shit?

163
00:10:21.630 --> 00:10:24.750
Mrs. Brown had us bleep all the swears so
we could show it at the school assembly.

164
00:10:24.760 --> 00:10:26.050
Yeah. which didn't make much sense

165
00:10:26.050 --> 00:10:28.670
because we were very clear
about it being R-rated.

166
00:10:28.680 --> 00:10:31.260
- Happy birthday. pal.
- This isn't happening.

167
00:10:31.260 --> 00:10:33.260
Oh. it's happening. Here we go.

168
00:10:34.890 --> 00:10:35.970
- God.
- Here. sit.

169
00:10:35.970 --> 00:10:38.180
Oh. I'm gonna kill you.

170
00:10:41.150 --> 00:10:43.360
I haven't changed a bit.

171
00:10:44.070 --> 00:10:45.610
<i>Holy ****!</i>

172
00:10:45.610 --> 00:10:46.530
Oh!

173
00:10:46.530 --> 00:10:48.900
- Look at the grass!
- Hot on the trail!

174
00:10:48.900 --> 00:10:51.360
- Look out for the quatch.
- Here we go.

175
00:10:51.370 --> 00:10:54.950
<i>Before you **** strike me.
I need to **** ask you one **** thing.</i>

176
00:10:54.950 --> 00:10:56.660
<i>You got some **** bite left?</i>

177
00:10:56.660 --> 00:10:57.620
<i>Or you all **** bark?</i>

178
00:10:57.620 --> 00:10:58.870
Boom!

179
00:10:58.870 --> 00:11:01.540
Damn. we'd been watching
a lot of Scorsese.

180
00:11:01.540 --> 00:11:03.670
We didn't quite have
the ear for it. did we?

181
00:11:03.670 --> 00:11:06.550
- I need to tell you something.
- What is it?

182
00:11:06.550 --> 00:11:09.630
<i>That I love you. I've always loved you.</i>

183
00:11:09.630 --> 00:11:11.380
And I always **** will.

184
00:11:11.390 --> 00:11:12.890
I **** love you too.

185
00:11:12.890 --> 00:11:14.850
Now. kiss me. woman.

186
00:11:16.350 --> 00:11:19.060
So much charisma. Already. you had it.

187
00:11:19.060 --> 00:11:21.640
I still can't believe I let Doug talk me
into doing that.

188
00:11:21.650 --> 00:11:23.480
What are you talking about?
That was your idea.

189
00:11:25.900 --> 00:11:27.030
Yeah!

190
00:11:27.650 --> 00:11:29.780
<i>- It's coming for us.</i>
- <i>We're trapped.</i>

191
00:11:29.780 --> 00:11:31.490
<i>What the hell are we gonna do?</i>

192
00:11:32.740 --> 00:11:33.570
- No!
- Yes.

193
00:11:34.120 --> 00:11:36.580
<i>Oh. my God. We're all gonna die!</i>

194
00:11:40.540 --> 00:11:42.160
This is where it gets real.

195
00:11:42.170 --> 00:11:44.540
<i>Not on my watch. mister.</i>

196
00:11:46.550 --> 00:11:48.250
- Boom!
- Yeah!

197
00:11:48.260 --> 00:11:50.130
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

198
00:11:50.130 --> 00:11:51.590
Amazing!

199
00:11:52.840 --> 00:11:54.220
So good!

200
00:11:55.680 --> 00:11:57.140
Whoo!

201
00:11:59.560 --> 00:12:02.480
That's probably the best birthday gift
I've ever received.

202
00:12:02.480 --> 00:12:04.900
- I didn't even know it existed.
- Well. I'm giving it to you.

203
00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:06.980
Plus the TV 'cause you can't get it out.

204
00:12:07.980 --> 00:12:09.190
- Yay!
- Yes!

205
00:12:12.900 --> 00:12:16.200
- It was right after. you know...
- Right after senior year of college.

206
00:12:16.200 --> 00:12:19.580
Yes. that's when <i>Anaconda</i> came out.
Remember? We saw it like 30 times.

207
00:12:19.580 --> 00:12:21.540
Put it right there alongside the classics.

208
00:12:21.540 --> 00:12:23.500
Totally. How about that cast? Come on.

209
00:12:23.500 --> 00:12:27.080
- J.Lo. Ice Cube. Owen Wilson. Stoltz.
- Oh. for sure.

210
00:12:27.090 --> 00:12:28.380
I mean. it's a murderers' row.

211
00:12:28.380 --> 00:12:33.220
Plus. that snake was like a metaphor
for our lives at that moment.

212
00:12:35.090 --> 00:12:37.600
Like. how life is coming at you. you know.

213
00:12:37.600 --> 00:12:40.560
hunting you and forcing you. like.

214
00:12:40.560 --> 00:12:41.810
off your...

215
00:12:42.680 --> 00:12:44.900
like your parents'
health insurance and stuff.

216
00:12:47.980 --> 00:12:49.690
- I don't know...
- No. that's true.

217
00:12:49.690 --> 00:12:51.110
- Yeah. that's...
- It was like that.

218
00:12:51.110 --> 00:12:52.570
- That's right. Kenny.
- Whatever.

219
00:12:52.570 --> 00:12:56.530
How about that accent by Jon Voight?
How about that? That was a choice.

220
00:12:56.530 --> 00:12:59.580
"They wrap
around you until you get the privilege

221
00:12:59.580 --> 00:13:01.660
- of hearing your bones break...
- Bones break...

222
00:13:01.660 --> 00:13:07.580
...before the power of embrace
causes your veins to explode."

223
00:13:08.250 --> 00:13:09.250
Sorry.

224
00:13:11.880 --> 00:13:13.800
I have the rights to <i>Anaconda.</i>

225
00:13:15.800 --> 00:13:16.840
What?

226
00:13:17.260 --> 00:13:18.930
I have the rights to <i>Anaconda.</i>

227
00:13:20.430 --> 00:13:21.680
Yeah.

228
00:13:21.680 --> 00:13:26.520
Apparently. the movie was based
on a novel by some dead Japanese guy.

229
00:13:26.520 --> 00:13:30.360
And my agent introduced me to his widow.

230
00:13:30.360 --> 00:13:35.570
Unbelievably. she was such a fan of the
four episodes that I did on <i>S.W.A.T...</i>

231
00:13:35.570 --> 00:13:37.780
- Who isn't?
- ...that she gave me the rights.

232
00:13:37.780 --> 00:13:40.870
Dude.
So what are you gonna do with them?

233
00:13:40.870 --> 00:13:42.580
Uh. well. not me.

234
00:13:43.910 --> 00:13:45.080
Us.

235
00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:49.170
We're gonna reboot the thing. Indie-style.

236
00:13:49.170 --> 00:13:53.590
Three weeks. run-and-gun in the Amazon.
Skeletal crew.

237
00:13:53.590 --> 00:13:56.800
Claire. you and I can star.
Kenny. you shoot it. Doug. you direct.

238
00:13:56.800 --> 00:13:59.390
Huh? Come on. What do you say?

239
00:13:59.390 --> 00:14:01.800
I mean. it's a wonderful idea
in theory. but...

240
00:14:01.810 --> 00:14:05.140
I'm in! I can get time off from work.

241
00:14:05.140 --> 00:14:06.850
Yes. you can. Kenny. Sweet!

242
00:14:06.850 --> 00:14:10.520
Kenny. what are you talking about?
You're in? He's not... No. He's not in.

243
00:14:10.520 --> 00:14:13.940
He says one thing and you're in already.
You're going to the Amazon.

244
00:14:13.940 --> 00:14:16.570
- He's not in.
- What do you say. Claire?

245
00:14:16.570 --> 00:14:18.200
- I... I just...
- Come on.

246
00:14:18.200 --> 00:14:20.070
I don't know if I'm
in the right headspace...

247
00:14:20.070 --> 00:14:21.320
- Of course you are.
- ...with the divorce.

248
00:14:21.320 --> 00:14:23.240
Of course you're not
in the right headspace.

249
00:14:23.240 --> 00:14:25.290
That's the best headspace.
Are you kidding me?

250
00:14:25.290 --> 00:14:28.620
Come on. it's like <i>Eat Pray Love</i>
and... shit.

251
00:14:28.620 --> 00:14:29.710
Come on.

252
00:14:30.500 --> 00:14:32.460
You know what? I'm in.

253
00:14:32.460 --> 00:14:34.960
- What? Really?
- Yes! Sweet.

254
00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:37.380
Yeah. I mean.
my life is totally shit anyway so...

255
00:14:37.380 --> 00:14:39.340
- God. I'm so happy to hear that.
- Hmm.

256
00:14:39.340 --> 00:14:42.010
I mean. not that your life is shit.
but that you're in.

257
00:14:42.010 --> 00:14:44.050
Besides. as soon as Doug says yes.

258
00:14:44.060 --> 00:14:46.020
we'll probably need you
to finance this whole thing.

259
00:14:46.020 --> 00:14:47.520
- What?
- Thank you.

260
00:14:47.520 --> 00:14:48.640
Doug?

261
00:14:52.900 --> 00:14:54.980
Griff. I'm sorry.

262
00:14:55.570 --> 00:14:59.320
I got responsibilities.
I got Malie. Charlie. my job.

263
00:14:59.320 --> 00:15:01.990
I know. Making wedding videos.

264
00:15:01.990 --> 00:15:03.490
Films. Right.

265
00:15:04.120 --> 00:15:05.790
It's a good life. you know?

266
00:15:06.330 --> 00:15:08.160
It's a B. B+ life.

267
00:15:09.290 --> 00:15:10.830
B. B+ life?

268
00:15:12.330 --> 00:15:13.540
It's a good life.

269
00:15:15.170 --> 00:15:16.550
Do you remember when we were kids

270
00:15:16.550 --> 00:15:18.210
and we would stay up
till 4:00 in the morning.

271
00:15:18.220 --> 00:15:20.880
hanging out in your mom's basement
watching horror movies?

272
00:15:21.590 --> 00:15:23.260
Scaring the shit out of ourselves.

273
00:15:23.260 --> 00:15:25.510
<i>Texas Chainsaw</i> on. like. repeat.

274
00:15:25.510 --> 00:15:28.100
Now we have the chance
to make one ourselves.

275
00:15:28.930 --> 00:15:31.810
Dude. it's what we dreamed about
ever since we were little kids.

276
00:15:33.560 --> 00:15:34.730
I hear ya.

277
00:15:35.730 --> 00:15:37.980
But we're not kids anymore. Griff.

278
00:15:38.570 --> 00:15:39.900
I'm sorry.

279
00:15:42.200 --> 00:15:43.910
Yeah. I know. All right.

280
00:15:44.910 --> 00:15:45.950
I just...

281
00:15:46.870 --> 00:15:48.040
I get it. I do.

282
00:15:48.950 --> 00:15:50.120
I get it.

283
00:15:55.670 --> 00:15:57.960
Still watching <i>The Quatch</i>.

284
00:16:03.550 --> 00:16:05.640
Charlie. why don't you go
check on those cookies?

285
00:16:05.640 --> 00:16:08.810
Okay. but I'm pausing it. so...

286
00:16:09.390 --> 00:16:10.390
don't touch it.

287
00:16:11.480 --> 00:16:13.560
Gonna need some ice-cold milch with that.

288
00:16:13.560 --> 00:16:14.900
You got it.

289
00:16:16.110 --> 00:16:17.610
- What are you doing?
- What?

290
00:16:17.610 --> 00:16:19.020
Just go make the movie.

291
00:16:19.030 --> 00:16:20.400
Malie.

292
00:16:20.400 --> 00:16:23.030
Come on. Every time you watch this thing.
you light up.

293
00:16:23.030 --> 00:16:26.200
Like I haven't seen you light up
in a long time.

294
00:16:26.200 --> 00:16:29.700
So what? I'm supposed to chase
some Hollywood fantasy I had as a kid?

295
00:16:29.700 --> 00:16:32.000
Waste a bunch of money and time.
and for what?

296
00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:34.290
In the end. what's it gonna change?

297
00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:37.880
Okay.

298
00:16:39.250 --> 00:16:40.260
Okay.

299
00:16:40.800 --> 00:16:41.800
Okay.

300
00:16:48.510 --> 00:16:51.560
<i>We hope you come to celebrate...</i>

301
00:16:51.560 --> 00:16:52.600
<i>As we become...</i>

302
00:16:52.600 --> 00:16:54.060
<i>The Hansons.</i>

303
00:16:55.650 --> 00:16:57.520
Holy shit.

304
00:17:01.610 --> 00:17:06.820
<i>♪ I don't want to wait
For our lives to be over ♪</i>

305
00:17:06.820 --> 00:17:09.330
<i>♪ I want to know right now ♪</i>

306
00:17:09.330 --> 00:17:11.580
- <i>♪ What will it be? ♪</i>
- <i>♪ ...what will it be? ♪</i>

307
00:17:12.830 --> 00:17:17.500
<i>♪ I don't want to wait
For our lives to be over ♪</i>

308
00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:19.920
What am I singing?

309
00:17:22.010 --> 00:17:23.010
Hey. dude.

310
00:17:25.090 --> 00:17:26.470
I don't want to wait. man.

311
00:17:28.720 --> 00:17:31.720
Our lives could be. like... over.

312
00:17:32.350 --> 00:17:33.640
What... What are you talking about?

313
00:17:33.640 --> 00:17:37.230
The <i>Anaconda</i> thing.
You were serious. right?

314
00:17:38.230 --> 00:17:39.270
Yes. very.

315
00:17:39.270 --> 00:17:40.770
Then let's do it.

316
00:17:41.780 --> 00:17:43.780
Let's reboot <i>Anaconda.</i>

317
00:17:43.780 --> 00:17:46.530
Yes! Yes.

318
00:17:57.460 --> 00:17:59.580
<i>♪ My anaconda don't ♪</i>

319
00:18:04.920 --> 00:18:06.930
<i>♪ My anaconda don't ♪</i>

320
00:18:07.840 --> 00:18:11.050
All right. budget-wise. soup to nuts.
what does it cost to get this thing made?

321
00:18:11.050 --> 00:18:14.890
I figure we need three weeks of shooting.
Some VFX. some SFX.

322
00:18:14.890 --> 00:18:18.190
a riverboat. a riverboat captain.
travel to and from a jungle.

323
00:18:18.190 --> 00:18:21.940
and a gigantic real snake.
preferably a rental.

324
00:18:21.940 --> 00:18:23.520
- Rental. copy.
- All in.

325
00:18:23.530 --> 00:18:25.530
two. two-and-a-half million dollars.

326
00:18:25.530 --> 00:18:27.240
That sounds right.

327
00:18:27.240 --> 00:18:31.620
We've approved a loan for you for up to...

328
00:18:31.620 --> 00:18:33.490
$9.400.

329
00:18:33.490 --> 00:18:34.830
Yes!

330
00:18:34.830 --> 00:18:37.620
I've revised the budget down to...

331
00:18:37.620 --> 00:18:39.040
$43.000 all in.

332
00:18:39.040 --> 00:18:40.420
That sounds more right.

333
00:18:40.420 --> 00:18:42.380
<i>Now. the film
does have to be scary. right?</i>

334
00:18:42.380 --> 00:18:46.300
Terrifying. But it can't just be about
a giant snake killing people.

335
00:18:46.300 --> 00:18:47.630
- Exactly.
- You know?

336
00:18:47.630 --> 00:18:49.760
It has to be about something. right?

337
00:18:49.760 --> 00:18:50.840
Right.

338
00:18:51.720 --> 00:18:53.140
I mean...

339
00:18:53.140 --> 00:18:54.260
- Themes.
- Themes.

340
00:18:55.220 --> 00:18:56.270
Come on.

341
00:18:56.270 --> 00:18:58.060
- Like grief.
- What about revenge?

342
00:18:58.060 --> 00:19:00.730
In terms of themes.
that's like one of the top ones.

343
00:19:00.730 --> 00:19:02.690
- Oh. my God. I got a good one.
- Hit me.

344
00:19:02.690 --> 00:19:04.610
Intergenerational trauma.

345
00:19:04.610 --> 00:19:06.780
I love intergenerational trauma.

346
00:19:06.780 --> 00:19:08.490
Who doesn't love intergenerational trauma?

347
00:19:08.490 --> 00:19:10.780
- It's the best.
- We're onto something here.

348
00:19:18.910 --> 00:19:20.330
This is a masterpiece.

349
00:19:20.330 --> 00:19:22.580
You're a goddamn genius. I love it.

350
00:19:22.580 --> 00:19:24.080
- Don't change a word.
- Not a word.

351
00:19:24.090 --> 00:19:26.460
Dude. you killed it. It's scary.
emotional. funny when it needs to be.

352
00:19:26.460 --> 00:19:28.920
- Romantic.
- Dude. thank you.

353
00:19:28.920 --> 00:19:30.260
Hey. Doug...

354
00:19:31.840 --> 00:19:35.260
I know that we had
our little dustup. but...

355
00:19:36.930 --> 00:19:38.680
I need to shoot this film. man.

356
00:19:38.680 --> 00:19:39.890
Dustup?

357
00:19:40.520 --> 00:19:43.940
Yeah. He fired me
from the wedding video stuff

358
00:19:43.940 --> 00:19:46.610
'cause I got a little wasted.

359
00:19:46.610 --> 00:19:48.150
He knocked over the wedding cake.

360
00:19:49.150 --> 00:19:51.990
- But I'm dealing with it.
- Like. getting sober?

361
00:19:51.990 --> 00:19:53.070
Yes.

362
00:19:53.070 --> 00:19:55.490
Well. I mean. Buffalo sober.

363
00:19:55.490 --> 00:19:56.490
Buffalo sober?

364
00:19:56.490 --> 00:19:57.910
Just beer and wine.

365
00:19:59.200 --> 00:20:02.870
And then some of the lighter liquors.
But definitely not all of 'em.

366
00:20:04.290 --> 00:20:05.250
I'm proud of you.

367
00:20:06.590 --> 00:20:07.800
Doug?

368
00:20:09.920 --> 00:20:12.670
If I'm being honest.
I enabled you a little bit.

369
00:20:12.680 --> 00:20:15.220
Of course you get a second chance.
Let's do this.

370
00:20:16.140 --> 00:20:17.140
- Nice!
- Thank you. man.

371
00:20:18.350 --> 00:20:19.810
Car's here.

372
00:20:19.810 --> 00:20:23.480
And you have the mefloquine. right?
You only take that once a week.

373
00:20:23.480 --> 00:20:26.270
- Hey. Dad. I almost forgot.
- Hmm?

374
00:20:26.270 --> 00:20:30.320
- Talk to me.
- But I got you this.

375
00:20:30.320 --> 00:20:31.820
What?

376
00:20:31.820 --> 00:20:33.200
I know. Pretty sick.

377
00:20:33.780 --> 00:20:36.620
"World's greatest Doug."

378
00:20:36.620 --> 00:20:39.280
- I thought it should say. "Dad."
- Whatever. man. it's funny.

379
00:20:39.290 --> 00:20:41.580
I love it. It's much better.

380
00:21:18.950 --> 00:21:21.240
- So it begins.
- Yeah!

381
00:21:21.240 --> 00:21:22.330
- Oh. yeah.
- All right.

382
00:21:22.330 --> 00:21:23.830
- Whoo!
- Made it.

383
00:21:23.830 --> 00:21:27.000
- Whoa. We're here.
- That's what I'm talkin' about!

384
00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:28.290
Brasília!

385
00:21:28.290 --> 00:21:29.210
Oh.

386
00:21:29.210 --> 00:21:31.880
So. hey. I was reading about anacondas
on the plane.

387
00:21:31.880 --> 00:21:34.840
Basically.
they wait in the water for days.

388
00:21:34.840 --> 00:21:37.930
stalking their prey.
never moving. just waiting.

389
00:21:37.930 --> 00:21:39.180
and then when a prey comes...

390
00:21:39.180 --> 00:21:41.050
...snatch and grab.

391
00:21:41.060 --> 00:21:43.850
Thousand pounds of pressure.
Think you're gonna get away? You're not.

392
00:21:43.850 --> 00:21:46.770
Crushing you. Oxygen leaving your lungs.

393
00:21:48.400 --> 00:21:49.980
Oh. God. it's terrible.

394
00:21:49.980 --> 00:21:52.650
- So. like in the movie <i>Anaconda</i>.
- Yeah. exactly.

395
00:21:52.650 --> 00:21:53.730
So it's real?

396
00:21:53.740 --> 00:21:54.990
Yeah. it's all real.

397
00:21:56.900 --> 00:21:58.700
Very real.

398
00:22:00.070 --> 00:22:02.830
There's this story about this woman...

399
00:22:03.450 --> 00:22:04.450
God bless her.

400
00:22:05.120 --> 00:22:07.670
The snake wraps around her so tight...

401
00:22:09.670 --> 00:22:11.290
the eyeballs just...

402
00:22:12.840 --> 00:22:14.800
- No.
- No way.

403
00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:16.880
Yeah. it was my grandmother. Sylvana.

404
00:22:16.880 --> 00:22:18.010
Shit.

405
00:22:18.010 --> 00:22:21.350
Horrible grandmother. But still sad.

406
00:22:21.350 --> 00:22:22.600
Huh.

407
00:22:22.600 --> 00:22:23.850
I'm sorry. who are you?

408
00:22:24.520 --> 00:22:27.520
Oh. I'm sorry. Carlos Santiago.
Yeah. you can call me Santiago.

409
00:22:27.520 --> 00:22:29.600
- Hey! It's Kenny.
- Yeah. hey.

410
00:22:29.600 --> 00:22:32.230
- Kenny from the phone. Hey.
- Kenny. Kenny. hey.

411
00:22:32.230 --> 00:22:34.400
- Hi.
- Yeah. this is our snake handler.

412
00:22:34.400 --> 00:22:35.400
Oh!

413
00:22:35.400 --> 00:22:37.240
- Thank God.
- He's supposed to be the best.

414
00:22:37.240 --> 00:22:39.400
No. "Supposed to be"?
We have a joker here.

415
00:22:39.410 --> 00:22:42.070
No. I am the best. Yes.

416
00:22:42.080 --> 00:22:43.160
- Oh. That's good.
- Yeah.

417
00:22:43.160 --> 00:22:45.330
So. welcome to Brazil.

418
00:22:46.450 --> 00:22:47.790
Let's meet the snake.

419
00:23:00.260 --> 00:23:02.720
Go around. we'll find her.

420
00:23:21.360 --> 00:23:24.240
When I found him.
he was dying of starvation.

421
00:23:25.030 --> 00:23:29.330
His food supply destroyed by gold miners
who put mercury in the river.

422
00:23:29.330 --> 00:23:32.250
- Gold miners?
- Gold mining poisons our land.

423
00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:35.920
Their greed almost killed my snake.

424
00:23:35.920 --> 00:23:37.500
- Oh.
- But I fed him.

425
00:23:37.510 --> 00:23:40.220
I nursed him back to life.

426
00:23:40.220 --> 00:23:43.840
and in many ways. he did the same for me.

427
00:23:43.850 --> 00:23:46.560
Ah. yes. A tale as old as time.

428
00:23:46.560 --> 00:23:48.520
Saved by a snake.

429
00:23:50.890 --> 00:23:52.230
What's your name?

430
00:23:52.230 --> 00:23:53.310
What's... Uh. Griff.

431
00:23:53.310 --> 00:23:55.570
Okay. Griff. He's not only a snake.

432
00:23:56.270 --> 00:23:58.440
He's my tiny giant. my friend.

433
00:23:59.360 --> 00:24:03.160
One of the most important creatures
of the herpetological world.

434
00:24:03.740 --> 00:24:05.320
No. of course... I... Sure.

435
00:24:05.320 --> 00:24:08.160
I didn't... I wasn't trying to...
I... Yes.

436
00:24:08.160 --> 00:24:11.330
Okay. Let me introduce you.

437
00:24:14.750 --> 00:24:16.080
Heitor.

438
00:24:16.090 --> 00:24:18.960
- Heitor?
- Oh. my goodness.

439
00:24:18.960 --> 00:24:20.630
Hey. cutie.

440
00:24:20.630 --> 00:24:23.090
- Oh. no. Not cutie.
- Oh. my...

441
00:24:23.090 --> 00:24:24.630
Oh...

442
00:24:24.640 --> 00:24:27.430
Oh. hell yes! This thing is nuts!

443
00:24:27.430 --> 00:24:30.970
There are rumors of 'condas even bigger.

444
00:24:30.980 --> 00:24:33.600
Maybe four or five times this size.

445
00:24:35.020 --> 00:24:36.350
Go ahead. Kenny from the phone.

446
00:24:36.360 --> 00:24:39.730
Um. is it true that
they regurgitate their prey?

447
00:24:39.730 --> 00:24:41.440
Um. sometimes.

448
00:24:41.440 --> 00:24:43.400
I mean. if you're lucky.

449
00:24:43.400 --> 00:24:46.490
you'd die right away because of...
...suffocation.

450
00:24:47.120 --> 00:24:51.120
But only the unlucky ones survive.

451
00:24:51.120 --> 00:24:52.410
Unlucky?

452
00:24:54.080 --> 00:24:58.460
Yeah. because then
you might actually be conscious

453
00:24:58.460 --> 00:25:02.340
when the snake comes back
to finish you off.

454
00:25:02.970 --> 00:25:04.470
- Gotcha.
- Ooh.

455
00:25:04.470 --> 00:25:05.840
Better to die.

456
00:25:15.100 --> 00:25:17.810
- Look at that boat!
- This is money in the bank. baby.

457
00:25:43.550 --> 00:25:45.470
Hey. Let me ask you a question.

458
00:25:45.470 --> 00:25:47.840
- Um. our snake guy...
- Mmm?

459
00:25:48.340 --> 00:25:51.010
Does he seem kind of batshit crazy?

460
00:25:51.010 --> 00:25:53.560
I mean. he's best friends with a snake.

461
00:25:53.560 --> 00:25:55.020
- Of course he's a little quirky.
- Yeah.

462
00:25:55.020 --> 00:25:56.100
But I like him.

463
00:25:56.100 --> 00:25:57.020
- Really?
- Yeah.

464
00:25:57.020 --> 00:25:58.100
But then again.

465
00:25:58.100 --> 00:26:00.230
I used up all my vacation days

466
00:26:00.230 --> 00:26:03.530
to come make a self-financed snake movie
with you three. so...

467
00:26:03.530 --> 00:26:05.740
- Yeah. your judgment is really off.
- My judgment is off.

468
00:26:05.740 --> 00:26:06.860
- It always has been.
- Exactly.

469
00:26:06.860 --> 00:26:08.910
Anybody talk to the captain?
It's time to shoot.

470
00:26:08.910 --> 00:26:11.070
I'll. uh. reach out again. boss.

471
00:26:11.990 --> 00:26:14.160
Hi. guys. My name is Ana.

472
00:26:14.160 --> 00:26:16.080
I believe you spoke
to my father on the phone?

473
00:26:16.660 --> 00:26:18.250
Bruno? That's your dad?

474
00:26:18.960 --> 00:26:20.170
Yeah. he sends his apologies.

475
00:26:20.170 --> 00:26:22.420
- but he's at the hospital.
- Oh.

476
00:26:22.420 --> 00:26:23.800
- Oh. I'm sorry.
- Unfortunately.

477
00:26:23.800 --> 00:26:25.710
you'll have to make other accommodations.

478
00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:28.930
'cause I need to take this boat upriver
for a routine service.

479
00:26:28.930 --> 00:26:30.470
But I can assure you a full refund.

480
00:26:30.470 --> 00:26:31.510
No. wait. Wait.

481
00:26:31.510 --> 00:26:33.510
- Everything else is booked.
- Yeah.

482
00:26:33.510 --> 00:26:35.390
And-- And w-we're gonna shoot a movie.

483
00:26:35.390 --> 00:26:37.100
It's a reboot of <i>Anaconda</i>.

484
00:26:37.100 --> 00:26:39.100
Technically.
it's more of a reimagining. but--

485
00:26:39.100 --> 00:26:41.060
It's actually more of a spiritual sequel.

486
00:26:41.060 --> 00:26:42.230
Good for you.

487
00:26:42.230 --> 00:26:44.270
- There's gotta be a way. right?
- We can crew the boat.

488
00:26:44.280 --> 00:26:45.360
There's nothing I can do...

489
00:26:45.360 --> 00:26:48.820
We have dreamed of making
this film together our entire lives.

490
00:26:48.820 --> 00:26:51.280
Please. I am begging you.

491
00:26:51.280 --> 00:26:53.330
- Please.
- Help us find another way.

492
00:26:53.330 --> 00:26:55.120
- Let's do this. but fast.
- Okay.

493
00:26:55.120 --> 00:26:56.620
- Yes! Let's go!
- Thank you!

494
00:27:17.520 --> 00:27:18.810
Whoo!

495
00:27:18.810 --> 00:27:20.770
- Oh!
- Wow!

496
00:27:20.770 --> 00:27:21.850
Yes!

497
00:27:21.850 --> 00:27:23.860
This is so beautiful.

498
00:27:23.860 --> 00:27:25.860
This is amazing. It's amazing.

499
00:27:27.900 --> 00:27:28.940
Looks exactly...

500
00:27:28.950 --> 00:27:30.030
Ooh. look!

501
00:27:31.740 --> 00:27:33.030
- Kenny?
- Yeah. bud?

502
00:27:33.030 --> 00:27:35.120
- How did you find this boat?
- Cocktail. anyone?

503
00:27:35.120 --> 00:27:37.080
- Nice!
- Ah!

504
00:27:37.080 --> 00:27:38.160
It's a computer.

505
00:27:40.500 --> 00:27:41.670
Yes!

506
00:27:44.840 --> 00:27:46.880
I want a list of all the boats

507
00:27:46.880 --> 00:27:49.050
that left the marina in the last 3 hours.

508
00:27:50.130 --> 00:27:51.220
Now!

509
00:28:00.180 --> 00:28:01.270
- Uh-oh.
- Oh.

510
00:28:01.270 --> 00:28:03.480
One more thing. you guys.
before we go to bed.

511
00:28:03.480 --> 00:28:05.270
We got a big day tomorrow.

512
00:28:05.270 --> 00:28:09.400
If you remember.
we had a tradition on all our films.

513
00:28:09.400 --> 00:28:11.280
The night before we started shooting.

514
00:28:11.280 --> 00:28:13.910
- we'd say a prayer to the movie gods...
- Mm-hmm.

515
00:28:13.910 --> 00:28:17.120
...asking them to basically
not screw us over.

516
00:28:17.120 --> 00:28:20.410
and for the first time ever.
may they listen.

517
00:28:20.410 --> 00:28:22.080
- Come on. to the movie gods.
- Yes.

518
00:28:38.260 --> 00:28:39.470
All right. We're rolling.

519
00:28:39.470 --> 00:28:42.350
<i>Anaconda.</i> scene 15. take one. Slap it.

520
00:28:42.350 --> 00:28:43.940
Bella!

521
00:28:45.100 --> 00:28:48.190
- What the hell are you still doing here?
- I've come to take you home.

522
00:28:48.190 --> 00:28:51.240
It's time you stopped chasing
this mythical snake.

523
00:28:51.990 --> 00:28:54.280
And what if I'm not prone to giving up?

524
00:28:54.780 --> 00:28:56.030
I didn't see you filming there.

525
00:28:56.570 --> 00:28:57.910
What are we doing? EPK?

526
00:28:57.910 --> 00:28:59.990
Background. DVD. bonus stuff.

527
00:28:59.990 --> 00:29:03.830
<i>The Anaconda</i> is a story
of an intrepid biologist played by Claire.

528
00:29:03.830 --> 00:29:09.460
<i>who hires an unhinged snake tracker
played by Griff.</i>

529
00:29:09.460 --> 00:29:12.260
to hunt down and kill
a giant. mythical 'conda

530
00:29:12.260 --> 00:29:13.590
that ate her entire family.

531
00:29:13.590 --> 00:29:16.550
Come and get me. you goddamn snake!

532
00:29:16.550 --> 00:29:18.800
And on a deeper level.
it's about chasing your dreams.

533
00:29:18.800 --> 00:29:24.270
And camera set. push-ups good. and action!

534
00:29:24.270 --> 00:29:25.690
What's it like shooting with Doug again?

535
00:29:25.690 --> 00:29:27.270
He and I are best friends.

536
00:29:27.270 --> 00:29:28.690
<i>We've worked together our whole lives.</i>

537
00:29:28.690 --> 00:29:30.610
<i>And I went out to LA.
and he was gonna come out.</i>

538
00:29:30.610 --> 00:29:33.360
We were gonna be a partnership.
and he didn't do it.

539
00:29:33.360 --> 00:29:37.700
Griff and I planned to work together
in LA. but. uh. you know. life intervened.

540
00:29:37.700 --> 00:29:39.370
But it doesn't matter.
'cause now we're together

541
00:29:39.370 --> 00:29:42.490
and now we're back. we're making this.
and it's as it should be.

542
00:29:42.500 --> 00:29:44.290
I am the insects.

543
00:29:45.250 --> 00:29:48.000
The anaconda moves slow and steady.

544
00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:49.170
Sometimes it goes fast.

545
00:29:49.170 --> 00:29:51.800
Snake POV. RD. Take 1.

546
00:29:52.510 --> 00:29:54.340
No. No. it's not working.

547
00:29:54.340 --> 00:29:57.010
Snake POV. the right way. Take 2.

548
00:29:57.840 --> 00:30:00.550
Sometimes he goes from above in the trees.

549
00:30:00.550 --> 00:30:02.680
sometimes from below in the water.

550
00:30:02.680 --> 00:30:06.890
The toothpick. it unlocked a couple
of aspects of this character for me.

551
00:30:06.890 --> 00:30:08.100
There's something there.

552
00:30:10.900 --> 00:30:11.730
Ah!

553
00:30:11.730 --> 00:30:14.190
Why would I be nervous
about doing a love story with Griff?

554
00:30:14.190 --> 00:30:15.440
You guys used to date.

555
00:30:15.990 --> 00:30:17.320
That was a long time ago.

556
00:30:17.320 --> 00:30:18.570
A little bit of chaos

557
00:30:18.570 --> 00:30:20.280
<i>is part of the ingredients.</i>

558
00:30:27.750 --> 00:30:29.000
<i>Maybe look at each other.</i>

559
00:30:29.000 --> 00:30:31.080
This might be the last time
you look at each other.

560
00:30:31.090 --> 00:30:33.130
You'd think you'd be
a little nicer to the guy

561
00:30:33.130 --> 00:30:35.000
who's out here to save your life.

562
00:30:35.010 --> 00:30:36.340
You're an asshole.

563
00:30:38.550 --> 00:30:39.550
Yeah.

564
00:30:40.390 --> 00:30:42.220
And a PhD.

565
00:30:45.600 --> 00:30:46.980
And cut.

566
00:30:46.980 --> 00:30:49.940
- Great stuff. guys. We got it.
- Whoo-hoo!

567
00:30:49.940 --> 00:30:52.860
Should we go one more time?
You wanna try it again?

568
00:30:52.860 --> 00:30:54.520
No. I'm good if you're good.

569
00:30:54.530 --> 00:30:55.940
Let's go one more time.

570
00:31:03.910 --> 00:31:07.790
- The chemistry between you two is...
- Yeah?

571
00:31:07.790 --> 00:31:10.080
Like we were right back in high school.

572
00:31:10.080 --> 00:31:11.500
When you looked up at her...

573
00:31:11.500 --> 00:31:12.830
Well. that's 'cause of your note.

574
00:31:12.840 --> 00:31:15.040
About taking the beat
right before you did it?

575
00:31:15.050 --> 00:31:17.010
Yeah. yeah. It made the scene.

576
00:31:17.590 --> 00:31:18.840
I tell you...

577
00:31:19.340 --> 00:31:21.680
I never felt like this
on <i>S.W.A.T.</i>

578
00:31:21.680 --> 00:31:23.970
I mean. granted
I was only in a couple of episodes.

579
00:31:23.970 --> 00:31:26.010
but it was never collaborative.
It was never fun.

580
00:31:26.020 --> 00:31:27.180
Not...

581
00:31:27.180 --> 00:31:28.850
Not like this. This. uh...

582
00:31:28.850 --> 00:31:31.440
- This is--
- Like we were back on <i>Quatch</i>?

583
00:31:33.310 --> 00:31:34.980
Yeah.

584
00:31:35.860 --> 00:31:36.860
Yeah.

585
00:31:43.200 --> 00:31:44.870
Do you guys have chupacabra?

586
00:31:45.620 --> 00:31:47.950
Ooh. That looks so good.

587
00:31:48.790 --> 00:31:49.830
Mm-mmm.

588
00:31:49.830 --> 00:31:52.460
Hey. so. one script thing.

589
00:31:52.460 --> 00:31:55.000
I was thinking. at the midway point.

590
00:31:55.000 --> 00:31:58.920
instead of. uh.
talking the bad guy out of it.

591
00:31:58.920 --> 00:32:00.470
what if...

592
00:32:00.470 --> 00:32:02.300
Claire's character...

593
00:32:03.470 --> 00:32:04.720
headbutts him?

594
00:32:04.720 --> 00:32:06.810
Sorry. Headbutts him?

595
00:32:07.470 --> 00:32:08.510
Headbutts him.

596
00:32:08.520 --> 00:32:10.600
Or... Or...

597
00:32:11.890 --> 00:32:12.890
we both do.

598
00:32:12.900 --> 00:32:14.400
Double headbutt.

599
00:32:14.400 --> 00:32:16.650
- Come on. It's kinda revolutionary.
- Double headbutt.

600
00:32:16.650 --> 00:32:18.150
That is super revolutionary.

601
00:32:18.150 --> 00:32:20.190
Why is that super revolutionary?

602
00:32:20.190 --> 00:32:22.360
Well. it's...
...never been done.

603
00:32:22.360 --> 00:32:25.740
Jesus Christ. This is a beautiful scene
with real stakes. Doug.

604
00:32:25.740 --> 00:32:27.280
Feel free to weigh in here.

605
00:32:27.280 --> 00:32:28.740
Nah. I hear you. I do.

606
00:32:28.740 --> 00:32:31.410
And. as always.
I trust your instincts on this.

607
00:32:32.960 --> 00:32:35.460
But a double headbutt
is pretty revolutionary.

608
00:32:35.460 --> 00:32:38.460
Right? It is--
It's very revolutionary. Yes.

609
00:32:38.460 --> 00:32:40.380
- There's no denying it.
- None!

610
00:32:40.380 --> 00:32:43.510
Oh. come on. Claire. Is the problem that
you don't know how to headbutt?

611
00:32:43.510 --> 00:32:45.890
Why would I not know how to headbutt?

612
00:32:45.890 --> 00:32:48.140
We're not born with these skills.
We learn them along the way.

613
00:32:48.140 --> 00:32:51.560
Let me show you.
Tight core. breathe in. hold that breath.

614
00:32:51.560 --> 00:32:52.930
- Yeah?
- Hi-yah!

615
00:32:52.940 --> 00:32:54.480
- And you can vocalize.
- Wow.

616
00:32:55.190 --> 00:32:59.730
Another kind of headbutt
is more unleashed. just full-on...

617
00:32:59.730 --> 00:33:01.230
Whoo!

618
00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:02.900
He got the arms in there. That's good.

619
00:33:02.900 --> 00:33:04.530
Send that shit into the goal.

620
00:33:04.530 --> 00:33:07.660
Or you put some Brazilian sauce on that.
You know?

621
00:33:07.660 --> 00:33:09.830
- And you go. boom! <i>Toma</i>!
- Oh!

622
00:33:09.830 --> 00:33:11.290
- <i>Toma</i>!
- <i>Toma</i>?

623
00:33:11.290 --> 00:33:12.500
Hey. I love it.

624
00:33:12.500 --> 00:33:13.790
Yeah. that's right.

625
00:33:13.790 --> 00:33:16.040
- Brazilian spice.
- Yeah!

626
00:33:16.040 --> 00:33:19.090
If I was gonna headbutt.
I would go for the bridge of the nose.

627
00:33:19.090 --> 00:33:21.300
- Yes.
- Just crack it. Hi-yah!

628
00:33:21.300 --> 00:33:24.130
- Jesus!
- Yes! That's it.

629
00:33:26.180 --> 00:33:28.550
- Jeez. Yeah. that's great.
- And you go. <i>"Toma! Toma!"</i>

630
00:33:29.470 --> 00:33:32.470
I think it's a different... <i>Toma</i>!

631
00:33:32.470 --> 00:33:34.270
- <i>Toma</i>!
- Yeah. <i>toma</i>!

632
00:33:35.810 --> 00:33:36.940
Goddamn!

633
00:34:28.450 --> 00:34:31.240
I'm sorry. but how could this happen. huh?

634
00:34:31.240 --> 00:34:33.120
Kenny. I thought you said
this guy was a pro.

635
00:34:33.120 --> 00:34:36.620
That's what he said. but he hasn't
provided us with a certificate.

636
00:34:36.620 --> 00:34:38.870
You fixed the crate. right?
It's taken care of?

637
00:34:38.870 --> 00:34:42.630
My thing. My job. Under control. All good.

638
00:34:43.500 --> 00:34:47.670
My Heitor. he's a beautiful. intelligent.
smart. sexy creature.

639
00:34:48.590 --> 00:34:50.760
He does exactly what I command.

640
00:34:51.550 --> 00:34:54.640
And I would never let anything happen

641
00:34:54.640 --> 00:34:59.390
to you or the crazy one.
or her. or her. or this "actor" here.

642
00:34:59.400 --> 00:35:01.860
- What the...
- So have a good night.

643
00:35:03.730 --> 00:35:08.860
May the sounds of the forest
be the music of your dreams.

644
00:35:11.030 --> 00:35:12.740
Jesus...

645
00:35:12.740 --> 00:35:14.700
Man. he's a poet.

646
00:35:28.670 --> 00:35:31.010
Okay. Actors. on your marks.

647
00:35:31.800 --> 00:35:33.300
Santiago. is Heitor ready?

648
00:35:33.300 --> 00:35:35.050
Yes. Heitor is always ready.

649
00:35:35.060 --> 00:35:37.520
Heitor is ready. and action!

650
00:35:42.310 --> 00:35:43.610
Cut. please.

651
00:35:44.860 --> 00:35:47.980
- Um. cut? All right. cut. Yeah.
- Yeah. I just-- Sorry. I need a little...

652
00:35:47.990 --> 00:35:49.440
Kenny. do you mind if I...

653
00:35:49.450 --> 00:35:51.740
Santiago. take five. Heitor. five.

654
00:35:52.530 --> 00:35:54.410
- Hey. Wow. that thing. it's really...
- Hey.

655
00:35:54.410 --> 00:35:57.450
It's huge when you see it
up close and personal like that.

656
00:35:57.450 --> 00:35:58.740
Majestic creature.

657
00:35:58.750 --> 00:36:00.830
But I just was wondering...

658
00:36:00.830 --> 00:36:05.590
I throw myself in front of the snake
to kind of protect Claire's character.

659
00:36:05.590 --> 00:36:06.840
- right?
- Correct.

660
00:36:06.840 --> 00:36:10.760
Is there any value in not doing that?

661
00:36:11.260 --> 00:36:12.470
What? No.

662
00:36:12.470 --> 00:36:15.550
- No. no. he sacrifices himself for her.
- Yeah. Of course.

663
00:36:15.550 --> 00:36:17.890
- It caps his arc. It's so important.
- Right. Right.

664
00:36:17.890 --> 00:36:21.100
- And also. dude. it's totally safe.
- Yeah.

665
00:36:21.100 --> 00:36:23.940
- Santiago has Heitor under control.
- Okay.

666
00:36:23.940 --> 00:36:27.110
- You've got nothing to worry about.
- Yeah. yeah. yeah. Yeah. yeah...

667
00:36:27.110 --> 00:36:29.150
- We're good. You're good.
- Yeah. Okay.

668
00:36:29.150 --> 00:36:30.940
- Okay.
- All right. let's do this.

669
00:36:30.940 --> 00:36:32.400
All right. take it from the top.

670
00:36:34.160 --> 00:36:35.200
Back to one.

671
00:36:36.370 --> 00:36:39.500
Santiago. Heitor? Action!

672
00:36:40.580 --> 00:36:41.580
Go!

673
00:36:42.580 --> 00:36:45.500
I'm not leaving! Not without you. Derek.

674
00:36:45.500 --> 00:36:48.630
This thing's got me.
The world's depending on you.

675
00:36:48.630 --> 00:36:50.670
I'm depending on you.

676
00:36:50.670 --> 00:36:53.420
Goddamn it! I love you. Derek van Hoyle!

677
00:36:53.430 --> 00:36:56.340
It's just-- I can't--

678
00:36:56.350 --> 00:36:59.470
- Put your face right up next to the snake.
- I don't like this.

679
00:36:59.470 --> 00:37:01.810
- I don't want to do it anymore.
- Get a tiny bit closer.

680
00:37:01.810 --> 00:37:03.640
Get closer. He's friendly.

681
00:37:03.640 --> 00:37:06.480
- I think you got it. dude!
- No. I don't quite have it!

682
00:37:06.480 --> 00:37:09.020
- Doug. you got the shot! You got the shot!
- Hold it! Just a couple more beats.

683
00:37:09.020 --> 00:37:11.360
This is gold.
Just give me one more second.

684
00:37:11.360 --> 00:37:13.570
One inch closer to your face.

685
00:37:13.570 --> 00:37:15.990
Get it right up in there!

686
00:37:15.990 --> 00:37:18.240
You're a hero! No!

687
00:37:18.240 --> 00:37:19.990
No!

688
00:37:39.640 --> 00:37:43.020
Oh. shit.

689
00:37:47.230 --> 00:37:49.900
I know you think this is strange.

690
00:37:51.690 --> 00:37:55.440
A grown man getting emotional
over some dead snake.

691
00:37:55.450 --> 00:37:56.610
Jesus.

692
00:37:57.160 --> 00:37:59.120
But I loved him.

693
00:37:59.120 --> 00:38:02.200
and he loved me back.
whatever way he could.

694
00:38:05.500 --> 00:38:08.000
God. No!

695
00:38:09.290 --> 00:38:11.040
Why is Kenny crying?

696
00:38:13.460 --> 00:38:14.670
Ugh!

697
00:38:14.670 --> 00:38:17.470
Hey. I don't want you here. Not for this!

698
00:38:17.470 --> 00:38:19.090
He tried to murder me.

699
00:38:19.090 --> 00:38:20.180
- Griff?
- What?

700
00:38:20.180 --> 00:38:22.930
- Let the man grieve.
- You murdered my friend.

701
00:38:22.930 --> 00:38:24.310
Just get out of my face.

702
00:38:24.310 --> 00:38:27.350
- What... Where am I supposed to go?
- Griff! Go! Just move!

703
00:38:27.350 --> 00:38:28.440
Fine!

704
00:38:49.710 --> 00:38:54.800
<i>♪ Go in peace. my friend ♪</i>

705
00:38:57.170 --> 00:39:02.600
<i>♪ May the divine snakes welcome you ♪</i>

706
00:39:02.600 --> 00:39:06.180
<i>♪ My dear friend ♪</i>

707
00:39:06.890 --> 00:39:10.390
- <i>♪ Snakedy snake ♪</i>
- <i>♪ Snakedy snake. yeah ♪</i>

708
00:39:10.400 --> 00:39:13.940
<i>♪ Snakedy snake ♪</i>

709
00:39:13.940 --> 00:39:17.820
<i>♪ May the divine snakes ♪</i>

710
00:39:17.820 --> 00:39:22.370
<i>♪ Welcome you. welcome you... ♪</i>

711
00:39:23.080 --> 00:39:24.620
What do you see?

712
00:39:25.790 --> 00:39:28.750
They're doing
some sort of weird snake funeral.

713
00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:31.580
Snake funeral?

714
00:39:55.820 --> 00:39:59.110
Sorry. I thought I heard something.

715
00:40:20.760 --> 00:40:21.880
<i>Timo?</i>

716
00:40:23.930 --> 00:40:25.010
<i>Timo!</i>

717
00:40:38.940 --> 00:40:41.860
- No. Not you. No. Just--
- I know. I'm sorry... I don't mean--

718
00:40:41.860 --> 00:40:44.360
- I'm not trying to disturb you.
- Just leave me alone.

719
00:40:44.360 --> 00:40:45.910
I'm sorry for your loss.

720
00:40:45.910 --> 00:40:48.830
I know you don't believe me.
but it's true. I really am.

721
00:40:48.830 --> 00:40:53.170
A friend of mine died once too.
and it hurts.

722
00:40:55.080 --> 00:40:56.080
Was it a snake?

723
00:40:56.670 --> 00:40:57.920
Was it a snake?

724
00:40:59.420 --> 00:41:00.630
No.

725
00:41:00.630 --> 00:41:04.630
It was just a... human person.

726
00:41:04.630 --> 00:41:05.840
Oh.

727
00:41:05.840 --> 00:41:07.390
Yeah. still sad. right?

728
00:41:08.760 --> 00:41:11.930
Totally.
Anyway. I just wanted to say I'm sorry.

729
00:41:12.980 --> 00:41:13.980
Beer?

730
00:41:14.850 --> 00:41:18.770
Well. I have my pills here. but. yeah.
Let's mix it up.

731
00:41:18.770 --> 00:41:23.860
A few commercials. TV.
Did a few episodes of <i>S.W.A.T</i>.

732
00:41:23.860 --> 00:41:25.490
- Oh! <i>S.W.A.T.?
-</i> Yeah.

733
00:41:25.490 --> 00:41:26.570
I like that one.

734
00:41:26.570 --> 00:41:30.990
I swear. I even had the last line--
Thanks.

735
00:41:30.990 --> 00:41:32.410
The last-- Thanks.

736
00:41:32.410 --> 00:41:34.870
- Last line of season three.
- So. what happened?

737
00:41:34.870 --> 00:41:37.960
Well. the producers decided that
they didn't really need that character.

738
00:41:37.960 --> 00:41:39.540
so they got rid of me.

739
00:41:40.670 --> 00:41:44.090
I mean. it's only been going
about eight or nine more seasons.

740
00:41:45.550 --> 00:41:46.550
They don't deserve you.

741
00:41:46.550 --> 00:41:48.720
Yeah. you're a star.

742
00:41:51.100 --> 00:41:53.600
- Thank you.
- Yeah. You've been in movies?

743
00:41:54.180 --> 00:41:57.100
- I'm in an industrial...
- You know what movie I like?

744
00:41:57.100 --> 00:41:59.730
- What?
- <i>The Legend of Bagger Vance.</i>

745
00:42:00.860 --> 00:42:04.110
- You should do a movie like that.
- Man. I wish.

746
00:42:04.110 --> 00:42:05.030
Yeah.

747
00:42:06.660 --> 00:42:09.160
- I like you.
- I like you too.

748
00:42:09.160 --> 00:42:10.450
- You know what?
- What?

749
00:42:10.450 --> 00:42:13.620
I'll get a new snake for your movie now.

750
00:42:13.620 --> 00:42:14.870
- Really?
- Yes.

751
00:42:14.870 --> 00:42:16.960
Oh. my God. Thank you so much.

752
00:42:16.960 --> 00:42:19.130
Yeah. You come with me. of course.

753
00:42:20.630 --> 00:42:21.460
What?

754
00:42:24.050 --> 00:42:26.930
Should we be in here?
Maybe we should head back.

755
00:42:31.220 --> 00:42:33.390
What was that?

756
00:42:33.970 --> 00:42:35.060
What was that?

757
00:42:37.440 --> 00:42:38.350
Listen.

758
00:42:39.480 --> 00:42:40.810
There are snakes around here.

759
00:42:41.310 --> 00:42:42.440
I can feel it.

760
00:42:43.690 --> 00:42:44.860
What does it feel like?

761
00:42:45.780 --> 00:42:48.740
I don't know. It's just very snaky.

762
00:42:48.740 --> 00:42:50.700
What's-- It's snaky?

763
00:42:53.120 --> 00:42:55.200
Ah.

764
00:42:58.250 --> 00:43:01.540
They hear from vibrations on the ground.

765
00:43:03.670 --> 00:43:06.050
Every step we take.

766
00:43:06.720 --> 00:43:09.010
drawing them closer.

767
00:43:10.340 --> 00:43:12.720
And when the jungle goes quiet...

768
00:43:16.270 --> 00:43:18.270
that's when you know they're close.

769
00:43:26.030 --> 00:43:27.150
Yeah.

770
00:43:35.080 --> 00:43:38.040
Hey. maybe we should
go back to the boat. huh?

771
00:43:38.040 --> 00:43:40.580
Think it'd be a good idea to go back
to the boat. Let's go back to the boat.

772
00:43:42.330 --> 00:43:43.540
Santiago.

773
00:43:44.340 --> 00:43:45.380
Santiago.

774
00:43:46.760 --> 00:43:47.880
Santiago!

775
00:43:52.090 --> 00:43:53.090
Nope.

776
00:44:16.120 --> 00:44:17.580
Where are you?

777
00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:38.010
Hey. Have you seen Santiago?
I don't think he's come back.

778
00:44:38.010 --> 00:44:42.100
- Back? From what?
- We went out to go get a new snake. We--

779
00:44:42.100 --> 00:44:44.690
You went to find a snake
in the middle of the night?

780
00:44:44.690 --> 00:44:47.020
Yeah. we need one for the movie.
It was dark. We got separated.

781
00:44:47.020 --> 00:44:48.190
It was crazy out there.

782
00:44:48.190 --> 00:44:49.690
- Griff. Griff. Griff. Griff.
- What?

783
00:44:49.690 --> 00:44:52.860
You went out in the middle of the night
to find a juicy snake in the jungle?

784
00:44:52.860 --> 00:44:54.570
You know what that's called?

785
00:44:55.620 --> 00:44:56.620
Producing.

786
00:44:57.620 --> 00:45:00.120
- Really?
- I guarantee he will be back

787
00:45:00.120 --> 00:45:04.960
with a giant snake.
and you and I are making movies.

788
00:45:04.960 --> 00:45:07.540
You're right. Santiago's a pro.
He'll be fine.

789
00:45:07.540 --> 00:45:09.920
If he's not back soon.
we'll go look for him.

790
00:45:32.740 --> 00:45:35.450
Thank you very much. Santiago.

791
00:45:38.950 --> 00:45:41.240
Guys. it's been over an hour.
I have to go find him.

792
00:45:41.240 --> 00:45:42.910
Well. you're not going alone.

793
00:45:42.910 --> 00:45:45.160
Yeah. we're definitely coming with you.
It's safer that way.

794
00:45:45.170 --> 00:45:47.500
Have you guys tried this thing?

795
00:45:48.040 --> 00:45:53.760
It's like a warm bowl of soup
but... ...but in chair form.

796
00:45:54.420 --> 00:45:55.840
Yeah. man. Chairs.

797
00:45:56.720 --> 00:45:58.260
They. like. hold you. man.

798
00:45:59.010 --> 00:46:01.350
They literally have arms. right?

799
00:46:03.100 --> 00:46:04.810
Oh. wow.

800
00:46:05.440 --> 00:46:07.230
Like when your parents are gone...

801
00:46:10.440 --> 00:46:12.190
we still have chairs. you know?

802
00:46:14.110 --> 00:46:16.320
What the hell are you talking about?

803
00:46:16.320 --> 00:46:18.240
Let's go find Santiago.

804
00:46:18.240 --> 00:46:20.200
Let's get a snake for our snake movie.

805
00:46:20.200 --> 00:46:22.330
Yeah. Santiago! Let's go!

806
00:46:29.880 --> 00:46:33.170
Hey. what direction
are we headed in?

807
00:46:33.710 --> 00:46:34.880
Um...

808
00:46:35.590 --> 00:46:36.800
Like. that way.

809
00:46:37.340 --> 00:46:39.890
Wait. Kenny. are you high right now?

810
00:46:39.890 --> 00:46:42.010
Yeah. but I'm good. I already peaked.

811
00:46:42.010 --> 00:46:43.390
Jesus Christ. Kenny.

812
00:46:43.390 --> 00:46:44.970
We're completely lost.

813
00:46:47.560 --> 00:46:49.900
Wait. You guys. this way.

814
00:46:50.480 --> 00:46:52.270
It looks like an old camper van.

815
00:47:09.750 --> 00:47:11.290
Ana is not on the boat.

816
00:47:11.290 --> 00:47:14.840
I need you to search the area.

817
00:47:14.840 --> 00:47:17.260
The men are scared to
go deeper into the jungle.

818
00:47:17.260 --> 00:47:19.630
<i>I don't care. we have to find her.</i>

819
00:47:24.720 --> 00:47:25.720
What is that?

820
00:47:25.720 --> 00:47:28.560
Oh.
maybe Santiago's sleeping in there.

821
00:47:28.560 --> 00:47:29.600
<i>Hola.</i>

822
00:47:32.310 --> 00:47:33.360
Whoa.

823
00:47:34.400 --> 00:47:37.360
Looks totally abandoned. Anybody home?

824
00:47:43.490 --> 00:47:45.030
Maybe some food and water.

825
00:47:45.030 --> 00:47:46.490
Yeah. We could stay here.

826
00:47:46.490 --> 00:47:47.700
At least tonight.

827
