879
00:51:48.070 --> 00:51:49.820
Griff.
can't you drive any faster?

880
00:51:51.450 --> 00:51:52.660
Whoa!

881
00:51:52.660 --> 00:51:54.490
Whoa. whoa. Ana. what are you doing?

882
00:51:55.410 --> 00:51:56.540
Whoa!

883
00:51:58.500 --> 00:52:01.000
- Kenny. are you getting this?
- Yes!

884
00:52:02.330 --> 00:52:03.670
Keep rolling!

885
00:52:06.710 --> 00:52:09.050
Griff. faster.

886
00:52:12.300 --> 00:52:13.640
Only one left.

887
00:52:37.290 --> 00:52:39.240
- Where is she?
- Oh. my God.

888
00:52:39.250 --> 00:52:40.370
Where is she?

889
00:52:43.460 --> 00:52:45.290
Who? Who do... Who do you mean?

890
00:52:45.290 --> 00:52:46.880
I know there's someone else here.

891
00:52:46.880 --> 00:52:49.090
So. where is she--

892
00:52:54.550 --> 00:52:55.550
Let's go. come on.

893
00:52:56.100 --> 00:52:57.180
We gotta go. Fast.

894
00:52:59.180 --> 00:53:01.180
Look. I can get you guys out of here.

895
00:53:01.180 --> 00:53:03.390
All we need to do is keep heading north.

896
00:53:03.900 --> 00:53:07.110
There's a small airport
about a day and a half from here.

897
00:53:07.110 --> 00:53:08.900
You can get us home?

898
00:53:08.900 --> 00:53:10.610
- Yes.
- Get us home.

899
00:53:10.610 --> 00:53:11.990
I think we gotta call it.

900
00:53:12.570 --> 00:53:15.320
Man. we've got such good stuff.
and we're so close.

901
00:53:15.820 --> 00:53:18.870
Really? We're going home?

902
00:53:18.870 --> 00:53:19.950
Buddy. I know.

903
00:53:19.950 --> 00:53:22.540
I don't wanna go home empty-handed either.

904
00:53:22.540 --> 00:53:25.330
But we came out here to make <i>Anaconda</i>.

905
00:53:25.830 --> 00:53:27.040
and now we're in it.

906
00:53:30.510 --> 00:53:31.630
Yeah.

907
00:53:35.430 --> 00:53:36.550
I'm sorry.

908
00:54:15.760 --> 00:54:18.930
Guys. emergency meeting.

909
00:54:18.930 --> 00:54:20.930
Cast and crew only. Kenny. sit down.

910
00:54:20.930 --> 00:54:22.760
- What is that?
- New pages.

911
00:54:22.770 --> 00:54:24.560
We have some time before the next port

912
00:54:24.560 --> 00:54:28.940
and I had an idea last night that I think
is just too damn good not to shoot.

913
00:54:28.940 --> 00:54:31.730
Doug. everybody's pretty burnt. man.

914
00:54:31.730 --> 00:54:33.980
Just hear me out.
I'm begging you please. Kenny.

915
00:54:33.990 --> 00:54:36.070
- All right. Sorry. boss.
- Thank you.

916
00:54:36.070 --> 00:54:39.030
What if you two. on your way
to find the anaconda.

917
00:54:39.030 --> 00:54:42.160
ran into a total badass
on an incredible quest?

918
00:54:42.160 --> 00:54:44.410
Oh. That's interesting.

919
00:54:44.410 --> 00:54:47.910
Let me guess.
to expose illegal gold miners?

920
00:54:47.920 --> 00:54:48.830
Bingo.

921
00:54:48.830 --> 00:54:50.960
- Raises the stakes.
- Exactly.

922
00:54:50.960 --> 00:54:52.960
And while they're hunting down
this mythical snake.

923
00:54:52.960 --> 00:54:55.130
they actually end up
fighting the real villain.

924
00:54:55.720 --> 00:54:56.720
An even bigger snake.

925
00:54:56.720 --> 00:54:59.260
- Man.
- Oh. yeah. Yes.

926
00:54:59.260 --> 00:55:00.550
Man.

927
00:55:00.550 --> 00:55:02.050
I like this.

928
00:55:02.680 --> 00:55:03.600
This is good.

929
00:55:03.600 --> 00:55:06.850
And if we add this element.
it does make the movie much bigger.

930
00:55:07.350 --> 00:55:09.810
Like. now. it's about something.

931
00:55:11.940 --> 00:55:12.860
Themes.

932
00:55:13.480 --> 00:55:15.400
Themes.

933
00:55:16.360 --> 00:55:17.450
Uh...

934
00:55:20.870 --> 00:55:21.950
Uh-huh.

935
00:55:21.950 --> 00:55:23.240
Yeah.

936
00:55:23.240 --> 00:55:25.120
Okay. guy-- You know what. guys?

937
00:55:25.120 --> 00:55:27.790
I didn't wanna say
anything before. but...

938
00:55:29.960 --> 00:55:31.670
this thing might be an Awards play.

939
00:55:33.420 --> 00:55:36.380
I mean. the Academy loves social horror.

940
00:55:36.380 --> 00:55:37.550
- Right?
- Yeah.

941
00:55:38.970 --> 00:55:42.600
Dude. you could be the white Jordan Peele.

942
00:55:43.140 --> 00:55:45.350
I was thinking the same thing.

943
00:55:48.680 --> 00:55:50.390
We've been through so much. you guys.

944
00:55:51.020 --> 00:55:52.730
Let's finish this movie.

945
00:55:55.020 --> 00:55:56.360
I'm in.

946
00:55:56.360 --> 00:55:57.610
- Let's do it.
- Yeah.

947
00:55:57.610 --> 00:56:03.070
Oh... Who are you gonna get to play
this new. awesome character?

948
00:56:06.910 --> 00:56:08.620
Ow!

949
00:56:10.250 --> 00:56:12.290
And cut. Yes!

950
00:56:12.290 --> 00:56:13.830
- Was it good?
- That's what I'm talking about.

951
00:56:13.830 --> 00:56:14.750
- Nice.
- Yeah.

952
00:56:14.750 --> 00:56:17.130
- You sure you've never acted before?
- I swear.

953
00:56:17.130 --> 00:56:19.010
Some of the best acting I've ever seen.

954
00:56:19.630 --> 00:56:22.130
- You're a natural. You're incredible.
- Thank you.

955
00:56:22.130 --> 00:56:23.890
Take five. Next up. we got 72.

956
00:56:24.720 --> 00:56:28.100
- Guys. you see what I'm saying?
- Yeah.

957
00:56:28.100 --> 00:56:29.770
- She's incredible. right?
- Yeah.

958
00:56:29.770 --> 00:56:31.940
Hey... ...a question. though.

959
00:56:31.940 --> 00:56:36.230
If-- If she saves us. it doesn't really
give my character anything to do.

960
00:56:36.230 --> 00:56:37.360
Yeah.

961
00:56:37.360 --> 00:56:41.490
This was supposed to be the moment where
my character starts falling for Derek.

962
00:56:41.490 --> 00:56:45.490
so he needs to do
something heroic. you know? Unselfish.

963
00:56:45.490 --> 00:56:48.120
I don't know. you guys.
this just feels like her moment.

964
00:56:48.120 --> 00:56:50.290
she actually did it in real life.

965
00:56:50.830 --> 00:56:53.370
But good news. I'm gonna shoot
all the rest on her

966
00:56:53.370 --> 00:56:55.210
so you guys have the day off.

967
00:56:55.710 --> 00:56:57.130
See you later.

968
00:56:58.210 --> 00:56:59.710
Take the day off.

969
00:57:01.130 --> 00:57:02.300
Huh.

970
00:57:08.140 --> 00:57:11.770
This is our movie. Griff.
and he's just cutting us out.

971
00:57:11.770 --> 00:57:13.690
Yep.
Welcome to show business. baby.

972
00:57:13.690 --> 00:57:16.980
You're not in it unless you're getting
screwed over by your friends.

973
00:57:18.570 --> 00:57:19.650
Yeah.

974
00:57:21.570 --> 00:57:25.200
You ever wake up and wonder
what the hell have I done with my life?

975
00:57:25.780 --> 00:57:28.580
- Oh. yeah. Like. every day.
- Mmm.

976
00:57:28.580 --> 00:57:31.160
Hey. at least you had the guts
to go after what you wanted.

977
00:57:31.160 --> 00:57:33.120
- No.
- You think I wanted to go to law school?

978
00:57:33.620 --> 00:57:35.420
What have I got to show
for it though. huh?

979
00:57:35.420 --> 00:57:36.500
You know what I have?

980
00:57:36.500 --> 00:57:40.460
I have a terrible apartment
and a 74-year-old roommate.

981
00:57:41.420 --> 00:57:45.550
Sometimes I go to Trader Joe's
just to feel air conditioning.

982
00:57:47.180 --> 00:57:48.640
You at least have a career.

983
00:57:50.140 --> 00:57:52.140
I mean. what do I have to show for it?

984
00:57:53.350 --> 00:57:56.350
I've got no family. No career.

985
00:57:57.270 --> 00:57:59.110
Never done anything that matters.

986
00:57:59.110 --> 00:58:00.650
No nothing.

987
00:58:03.070 --> 00:58:04.280
It's never too late.

988
00:58:13.500 --> 00:58:15.160
<i>Griff. I know you're in there.</i>

989
00:58:15.160 --> 00:58:16.540
<i>Let's make a movie.</i>

990
00:58:19.880 --> 00:58:20.960
Ugh.

991
00:58:20.960 --> 00:58:22.050
<i>Hola. amigo.</i>

992
00:58:22.050 --> 00:58:24.960
Jesus. Come on. get dressed.
We've got a packed day.

993
00:58:24.970 --> 00:58:26.550
What are you talking about?
I am dressed.

994
00:58:26.550 --> 00:58:28.680
I'm dressed really...
very nicely.

995
00:58:28.680 --> 00:58:30.640
All right. Can you just
take a cold shower?

996
00:58:30.640 --> 00:58:32.060
We gotta film. like. now.

